  "prompt_text": "Design a database schema for a library management system with books, patrons, and loans.",
  "response_text": "For this library management system, we will design a relational database schema with three main tables: Books, Patrons, and Loans.\n\n1. **Books** table:\n   - book_id (Primary Key, Integer)\n   - title (Text)\n   - author (Text)\n   - publication_year (Integer)\n   - genre (Text)\n   - available (Boolean)\n\n2. **Patrons** table:\n   - patron_id (Primary Key, Integer)\n   - first_name (Text)\n   - last_name (Text)\n   - email (Text, unique)\n   - phone_number (Text)\n   - address (Text)\n\n3. **Loans** table:\n   - loan_id (Primary Key, Integer)\n   - book_id (Foreign Key, references Books.book_id)\n   - patron_id (Foreign Key, references Patrons.patron_id)\n   - loan_date (Date)\n   - return_date (Date)\n   - extension (Integer, default 0)\n\nThe Loans table has a foreign key relationship with both the Books and Patrons tables. The extension field is used to track any extensions on the loan. If a book is currently on loan, the 'available' field in the Books table will be set to false.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 9\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
